Title: Multitasking Memory Test - Learn some gesture symbols and remember sequences.  Test your memory!
Description: Part 1: Learn a set of 20 gesture symbols. Part 2: Memory Test - Remember sequences of words and gestures
Answer.Comments: Thank you for this study -- it allowed me to experiment with different ways to remember words and try to figure out which way works best for me. At first, I just kept repeating the string of words to myself but then I discovered that I remembered better if I made up a story with the words. Later, I discovered that silently visualizing the story was nearly as helpful as saying it out loud. One suggestion: this was a long survey requiring intense focus, so allowing a 2-3 minute break in the middle would have been much appreciated (perhaps allow a 3 minute pause right after the gestures refresher test). THANKS!
